description: Borrowed from French caïque, from Italian caicco, from Ottoman Turkish قایق‎ (kayık), from Proto-Turkic *kiayguk (“boat, oar”). Cognate with modern Turkish kayık.

entries.meaning: (nautical) A small wooden trading vessel, brightly painted and rigged for sail, traditionally used for fishing and trawling.

description: From Spanish caíque or Portuguese caíque.

entries.meaning: Any of four (previously two) species of parrot in the genus Pionites.
